title: "Tell me what you know about this place"
tags: lore_dump
---
<<if $companion_type == "scholar">>
    "The ancient texts called it the Sundered Realm. A place where reality was... reorganized. But the descriptions were fragmentary, written by survivors who could barely comprehend what they'd witnessed."
    
    The scholar's voice drops to a whisper: "They spoke of tiles of existence, floating in a void between worlds. And something that... arranged them."
<<elseif $companion_type == "guide">>
    "I've heard rumors from other travelers. They said the landscape changes when you're not looking. That paths lead to places they shouldn't. That the very ground remembers things it should have forgotten."
    
    The guide shudders: "I thought they were just stories meant to scare children."
<<else>>
    "I... I don't know much. Just that people who come here... they change. The lucky ones come back different. The unlucky ones..."
    
    Your companion's voice trails off, unable to finish the thought.
<<endif>>

<<set $dread_level += 2>>
<<set $companion_stress += 3>>

-> Press for more details
-> Reassure them
-> Change the subject

